{
  "title": "Encounter · class → visit_concept_id",
  "notes": "Branch dimension: how the Encounter__visit_occurrence edge derives `visit_concept_id` from `Encounter.class.code` (HL7 v3 ActEncounterCode), plus the core columns of the visit_occurrence FK hub.\n\nGrounded in mapspec/etl/Encounter__visit_occurrence.sql + mapspec/views/Encounter__visit_occurrence.view.json + cm.encounter_class_to_omop (materialized from mapspec/profiles/encounter-class-to-omop.cm.json):\n\n  visit_occurrence_id    = referenceToId(Encounter.id)            -- surrogate PK, not asserted\n  person_id              = referenceToId(subject.getReferenceKey())\n  visit_concept_id       = COALESCE(cls.concept_id, 0)            -- cls = cm.encounter_class_to_omop ON source_code = class.code\n  visit_start_date       = (period.start ::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC')::date\n  visit_start_datetime   = (period.start ::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC')\n  visit_end_date         = (COALESCE(period.end, period.start)::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC')::date\n  visit_end_datetime     = (COALESCE(period.end, period.start)::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC')\n  visit_type_concept_id  = 32827  (constant — 'EHR encounter record')\n  provider_id            = referenceToId(participant.first().individual.getReferenceKey())\n  care_site_id           = referenceToId(serviceProvider.getReferenceKey())\n  visit_source_value     = Encounter.id (FHIR resource UUID, traceability anchor)\n  visit_source_concept_id        = 0 (constant)\n  admitted_from_concept_id       = 0 (constant); admitted_from_source_value   = hospitalization.admitSource.coding.first().code (Synthea omits → NULL)\n  discharged_to_concept_id       = 0 (constant); discharged_to_source_value   = hospitalization.dischargeDisposition.coding.first().code (Synthea omits → NULL)\n  preceding_visit_occurrence_id  = referenceToId(partOf.getReferenceKey()) (no partOf → NULL)\n\nCLASS → CONCEPT (cm.encounter_class_to_omop, v3-ActCode group, all verified standard 'S' Visit concepts in vocab.concept):\n  AMB     → 9202 Outpatient Visit\n  EMER    → 9203 Emergency Room Visit\n  IMP     → 9201 Inpatient Visit\n  VR      → 722455 Telehealth\n  HH      → 581476 Home Visit (also FLD)\n  SS      → 8870 Emergency Room - Hospital (also urgentcare)\n  snf     → 8676 Nursing Facility\n  hospice → 8546 Hospice\n  NONAC   → 42898160 Non-hospital institution Visit\n  (also in cm but same concept as a covered class: ACUTE→9201, OBSENC/PRENC/outpatient/wellness/ambulatory→9202, emergency→9203, inpatient→9201, virtual→722455)\n  (unmapped class code) → no cm row → COALESCE(...,0) = 0\nSynthea only ever emits AMB / EMER / VR / IMP / HH classes (AMB dominates, 6072/6388); SS / snf / hospice / NONAC are valid cm.encounter_class_to_omop entries with distinct standard Visit concepts that Synthea never emits but the lookup join must still resolve correctly. The unmapped-class and no-end and status-filter variants below are synthetic — Synthea ships every encounter status='finished' with both period.start and period.end — but they exercise the COALESCE(class)→0 fallback, the COALESCE(period.end, period.start) end-fallback, and the status WHERE filter directly.\n\nTIMEZONE NORMALIZATION (load-bearing): Synthea FHIR stamps period in the generator's local TZ ('…+01:00'); the SQL re-anchors to UTC via `::timestamptz AT TIME ZONE 'UTC'` so the diff against cdm.visit_occurrence (UTC) matches. All timestamps below carry an explicit 'Z' (==+00:00) offset so the produced wall-clock equals the literal input — no shift. (Verified against real rows: a '+00:00' encounter keeps its wall-clock; a '+01:00' encounter shifts -1h.)\n\nSTATUS FILTER: stage-2 WHERE drops status IN ('entered-in-error','cancelled','planned','unknown') so non-events never become a visit row. An 'entered-in-error' encounter therefore produces zero rows (negative case, omop: {}).\n\nISOLATION: for fhir.encounter the only PLAN edge is Encounter__visit_occurrence → visit_occurrence, so the runner produces only that table. The Patient (patient-1) and Practitioner/Organization stubs are present ONLY to anchor reference resolution (their own edges are NOT run because person/provider/care_site are not asserted tables) — person_id/provider_id/care_site_id are just referenceToId() of the bare logical ids.\n\nNON-VARYING CONTEXT held constant so only class/period vary: single Patient subject patient-1, one Practitioner prac-1 (provider_id), one Organization org-1 (care_site_id); no partOf (preceding_visit_occurrence_id NULL); no hospitalization (admitted_from / discharged_to source values NULL, concept_ids 0).",
